preibisch_imagej.axis

Class Axes

  • java.lang.Object
    • preibisch_imagej.axis.Axes

  • public final class Axes
extends Object
    An extensible enumeration of dimensional AxisTypes. Provides a core set (X, Y, Z, TIME and CHANNEL) of axis types. The get(java.lang.String) methods can be used to create new, custom axis types which will be cached for future use.
    Author:
    Curtis Rueden, Mark Hiner

    • Method Detail

      • get

        public static AxisType get(String label)
        Accessor for an AxisType of the given label. Creates and caches the AxisType as a non-spatial axis if it does not already exist.

      • get

        public static AxisType get(String label,
                           boolean spatial)
        Accessor for an AxisType of the given label. Creates and caches the AxisType with the given label and spatial flag if it does not already exist.

      • knownTypes

        public static AxisType[] knownTypes()
        Returns:
        an array of AxisTypes corresponding to all currently defined axes.

      • unknown

        public static AxisType unknown()
        Gets an "unknown" axis type.

        Always returns a new object, which is not part of the extended enumeration. In this way, two unknown axis types are never equal.
